The course consists of two parts - the theoretical and practical ones. The theoretical part looks at the cultural scene as a whole, its main trends in architecture and the visual arts in order to point out their influence on the evolution of literary styles and provide the necessary wider cultural background for the close reading  a selection of period texts better to understand the interdeterminacy of the cultural phenomena and highlight the ground principles of different literary styles and trends. The course is richly illustrated with pictorial material. Texts discussed in class can be found in the course book.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is designed to give an overview of the main trends in English literature from romanticism to modernism. The analysis of literary phenomena is closely tied to their historical context and parallel developments in the figurative arts and architecture to provide a fully rounded picture of the period.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course is designed to help the student to understand the evolution of different styles and trends in English literature in the given period, to put them in their proper historical context and view these phenomena as part of the broader cultural scene. The student should be able to recognize and differentiate between different period styles and their peculiarities as manifest in the texts discussed in class.
